{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"130\t`cledger scan [--paranoid]`: Standalone check with exit 1 on findings — CI-friendly.\n131\t\n132\t### Maximum safety recipe\n133\t\n134\tKeep all defaults (capture and sync scan on), add repo-specific patterns in `.cledger.json` for domain-specific secrets, enable env masking only if `.env` holds secrets (not config), run `cledger scan` in CI, and treat `--no-scan` as a deliberate exception you document.\n135\t\n136\t## Roadmap\n137\t\n138\t- **Path-based capture exclusion** — the path half of the redaction config\n139\t  (\"never record reads of `secrets/**`\"); requires correlating `tool_use`\n140\t  file paths with their `tool_result` events.\n141\t- **Post-push purge** — true content removal after the ledger ref has been\n142\t  shared (force-push + collaborator re-fetch coordination); the local\n143\t  pre-push squash shipped with `cledger redact`.\n144\t- **`re-anchor`** — reattach events orphaned by squash merges or history\n145\t  rewrites. The desired end state is that this happens by default: a squash\n146\t  commit should end up carrying the conversations of the branch it squashed.\n147\t  Hard part: squashes often happen off-machine (GitHub \"Squash and merge\"),\n148\t  so detection needs patch-id/branch-tip matching after fetch, not a local\n149\t  hook.\n150\t- **Harness-artifact capture** — decide whether the ledger should also\n151\t  preserve valuable non-git-controlled agent artifacts that normally die\n152\t  with a worktree or live outside the repo (e.g. Claude Code auto-memory\n153\t  directories, session state). They fit the `document` kind; the question is\n154\t  scope and capture triggers.\n155\t- **Format-drift: raw preservation** — adapters now count and warn about\n156\t  transcript line types they don't recognize (the detection half shipped in\n157\t  0.4.0), but those lines are still not stored. Possibly preserve them\n158\t  raw-only so a later adapter version can re-normalize them.\n159\t- **Purge tooling** — true content removal behind a `redaction` event.\n160\t- **Sub-turn citation anchors** for downstream consumers like intent-recall.\n161\t\n162\t## Storage model, in one paragraph\n163\t\n164\tOne git note per anchor commit under `refs/notes/conversation-ledger`; the\n165\tnote body is one canonical-JSON event per line, sorted and unique, with all\n166\tcontent inline (GC-safe, no out-of-repo pointers). Concurrent branches merge\n167\tconflict-free via git's `cat_sort_uniq` notes strategy. Events record\n168\trepository, branch, HEAD, dirty-tree fingerprint, actor, timestamps, and\n169\tcapture mechanism. Redaction appends a `redaction` event rather than silently","tool_use_id":"toolu_01NRgGHRuBuZNG86WKVkYSMe","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"db9dee3b20ece4c8d09a3feb50ecf84b70c566c31b152350e8bd060a46d4b1d3","head":"82fdd94dda136dcaa0c4d769bbd2f84668eb465e","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:1adc3903-054a-4c3f-b176-50dc694bfab9","seq":35},"id":"ev1-c500677bb0d5a04a45f2f5489fcee983b603bebf6b838df1814435d26a40b58d","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T16:15:49.734Z","producer":{"session_id":"1adc3903-054a-4c3f-b176-50dc694bfab9","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.5.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"content":"130\t`cledger scan [--paranoid]`: Standalone check with exit 1 on findings — CI-friendly.\n131\t\n132\t### Maximum safety recipe\n133\t\n134\tKeep all defaults (capture and sync scan on), add repo-specific patterns in `.cledger.json` for domain-specific secrets, enable env masking only if `.env` holds secrets (not config), run `cledger