{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"No tests pin the warning wording or `KNOWN_KINDS` — I'm free to change both. Here's the design I'm committing to, then I'll build it.\n\n## Design: `unrecognized` preservation events\n\nWhen an adapter hits a line type in neither its convertible nor known-skipped set, instead of *count-and-drop* it now *counts and emits a preservation event*:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"kind\": \"unrecognized\",\n  \"occurred_at\": \"<line timestamp, else session base time>\",\n  \"actor\": { \"type\": \"system\" },              // not attributed — we didn't interpret it\n  \"producer\": { \"tool\": \"cledger\", \"source\": \"...\", \"session_id\": \"...\" },\n  \"conversation\": { \"id\": \"...\", \"seq\": <line index> },\n  \"content\": { \"unrecognized_type\": \"<type key>\" },   // tiny, non-interpreted label\n  \"raw\": { \"format\": \"<native-format-version>\", \"data\": <full parsed line> }\n}\n```\n\nWhy this shape:\n- **Identity/idempotency falls out of `seq`.** Line index is already in the identity subset, exactly as recognized turns rely on it — so distinct lines get distinct ids, and re-scanning the same line dedups. `raw` staying out of identity is *correct* here (matches convention; format-version bumps never churn ids).\n- **Lossless & \"raw-only\"** — the whole line lives under `raw.data`, uninterpreted.\n- **Secrets removed by construction** (your concern): it rides the normal `appendEvents` → `redactDraft` path, which walks `raw.data`, so the capture-tier redaction stack covers preserved lines with zero new code. I'll add an explicit test proving a token inside an unrecognized line gets redacted.\n- **Re-normalizable**: `kind === \"unrecognized\"` + `raw.format` let a future adapter find these, re-parse, and supersede them.\n\nLet me set up task tracking and implement.","type":"text"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger"